\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. O. spinosa} (L.) Sweet, {\i Hort. Brit.} ed. 2, 225 (1830) ({\i Sedum spinosum} L.). Rosette-leaves 15-25 × 3-5 mm, oblong, tapered suddenly to a terminal spine 2-4 mm. Stem 10-30 cm; cauline leaves alternate, similar to the basal leaves but smaller. Raceme 5-20 cm, very dense; pedicels 0-1 mm. Petals 4 mm, lanceolate, acute, greenish-yellow. Anthers yellow. Follicles 5-6 mm.{\i  Dry rocks and stony ground. E. Russia} ({\i S. Ural}). Rs(E). ({\i N. & C. Asia.})
