\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. O. thyrsiflora} (DC.) Fischer ex Sweet, {\i loc. cit. }(1830). Like {\b 1} but rosette-leaves 6-8 mm, broadly elliptical or suborbicular, with a shorter spine; cauline leaves strongly keeled, almost triquetrous; raceme broader and laxer, the lower flowers clearly pedicellate; petals white or pinkish; anthers dark purple.{\i  Dry rocks and stony ground. E. Russia.} Rs(C, E). ({\i C. Asia}.)
